#!/usr/bin/env bash
cat <<'EOF'

============================================================
Manual steps still required (cannot be automated):
  1. Plug YubiKey, register FIDO2 at https://aka.ms/fido2
     and ensure passkey is enrolled in
     https://mysignins.microsoft.com/security-info
     GDM smartcard login is disabled by bootstrap so the key does not block
     password login at boot.
  2. Install the Linux Entra SSO browser extension in Firefox/Chrome/Brave:
     https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/linux-entra-sso/jlnfnnolkbjieggibinobhkjdfbpcohn
  3. Edit /etc/himmelblau/user-map and replace the commented example with your
     local-user -> user@microsoft.com mapping.
  4. Run: sudo aad-tool auth-test --name <local-user>
     Use the same password as your local account for the Hello PIN so login can
     auto-unlock the TPM secret.
  5. Confirm the device shows up as compliant in
     https://portal.manage-beta.microsoft.com/devices
  6. Optional: once enrollment works, install the user-session broker:
     sudo apt install himmelblau-broker
  7. Azure VPN: import https://aka.ms/AzVPN-Temp into the
     Microsoft Azure VPN Client GUI.
  8. Clone work repos under ~/repos (see git.md).
============================================================
EOF